---
title: Chipotle Seitan Chili with Black Beans and Bell Pepper
description: While beans are the basis for any good vegetarian chili, sometimes you just want a little bit more oomph in your bowl. Here, we’re using seitan to lend extra heartiness to this dish. Seasoned with chipotle spice, the wheat-based protein has smoky, sultry flavor built right in. Served on top a bed of white rice and garnished with shreds of melty cheese, this chili is comfort food at its finest.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/seitan-chili-628cebf6.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/seitan-chili-dc97c7dc.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/seitan-chili-5835b8a79f236a7d06343fb2
course: main course
cuisine: North America
servings: 2
author: HelloFresh
time required: 35 minutes
nutrition:
  calories: 696 kcal
  fat: 13 g
  saturated fat: 3 g
  carbohydrates: 83 g
  sugar: 10 g
  protein: 52 g
  fiber: 10 g
  sodium: 889 mg
---

Bring @water{1%cup} to a boil in a small #pot. Once boiling, add @Jasmine Rice{1/2%cup}, cover, and reduce to a simmer. Cook until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}. Keep covered.

Wash and dry all produce. Mince or grate @Garlic{2%clove}(minced). Halve, seed, and remove white ribs from @Red Bell Pepper{1}(halved, seeded, and finely diced), then finely dice. Halve, peel, and dice @Red Onion{1}(diced). Thinly slice @Scallions{2}(thinly sliced), keeping greens and whites separate. Core and dice @Roma Tomato{1}(diced). Drain and rinse @Black Beans{1%box}(drained and rinsed).

Heat a large drizzle of @Olive Oil{teaspoon} in a large pan over medium heat. Add bell pepper, onion, and scallion whites and cook until softened, ~{3-5%minutes}, tossing occasionally.

Stir in garlic, tomato, and @Chipotle Seitan Crumbles{8%ounce}. Break seitan into small pieces with #spatula or #wooden spoon. Cook until slightly reduced, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Stir in black beans, @Veggie Stock Concentrate{1}, and @water{1%cup}. Simmer until thickened, ~{5-7%minutes}. Season with @Salt and @Pepper.

Divide rice between plates. Top with chili. Garnish with scallion greens and @Cheddar Cheese{1/4%cup}(shredded).

> We sent more cheddar cheese - feel free to add extra!